you remember me like the others.

327
00:26:03,504 --> 00:26:05,891
You said "like the others."
I'm sorry!

328
00:26:25,930 --> 00:26:27,233
Claire!

329
00:26:27,233 --> 00:26:28,956
The stewardess is Claire!

330
00:26:29,328 --> 00:26:31,542
Yes, yes, yes, yes! I assure you.
it's Claire!

331
00:26:31,923 --> 00:26:33,445
Is that what you think?

332
00:27:21,119 --> 00:27:22,771
What will it be, Mademoiselle Mani?

333
00:27:22,771 --> 00:27:26,299
Cognac.
Oh, yes. Cognac!

334
00:27:31,553 --> 00:27:33,120
What are you doing here alone?

335
00:27:33,120 --> 00:27:34,825
You're drinking cognac?!

336
00:27:34,825 --> 00:27:36,760
Isn't that amazing?
- Yes!

337
00:27:37,558 --> 00:27:38,920
Why?

338
00:27:38,920 --> 00:27:40,809
It's weird seeing you
alone in a bar.

339
00:27:40,809 --> 00:27:42,713
when I just saw
something incredible!

340
00:27:43,693 --> 00:27:45,147
What's unbelievable?

341
00:27:45,147 --> 00:27:48,003
I can't say.
Pay up and let's go!

342
00:27:49,264 --> 00:27:51,347
Well, are you coming?
The car's waiting.

343
00:27:51,347 --> 00:27:52,773
Does that remind you of anything?

344
00:27:52,773 --> 00:27:55,083
How do you know?
- It's not hard to guess!

345
00:27:56,361 --> 00:27:58,984
Uh, do you drink cognac?
- She drank to her memories.

346
00:27:59,368 --> 00:28:02,563
Aha! I couldn't get away
from those two guys! - You didn't?

347
00:28:03,266 --> 00:28:05,862
They've been asking me
a bunch of questions about you.

348
00:28:06,116 --> 00:28:08,778
These two are friends of mine from the war.
from the war, the good guys!

349
00:28:12,406 --> 00:28:15,346
So you met!
What did he say to you?

350
00:28:15,346 --> 00:28:18,507
Who? - Don't make me
a fool! Forestier.

351
00:28:44,815 --> 00:28:46,609
Well, there you go.
- Thank you.

352
00:28:47,975 --> 00:28:50,688
Why don't we have dinner together?
- Oh, no, I'm exhausted.

353
00:28:51,785 --> 00:28:54,207
I need a shower
and my bed.

354
00:28:59,951 --> 00:29:01,309
Going to your place?

355
00:29:01,886 --> 00:29:03,896
Oh, mademoiselle, first.
I'll take my things first,

356
00:29:03,896 --> 00:29:06,037
and then, if I'm not too
tired, I'll go for a drink.

357
00:29:06,037 --> 00:29:07,792
with two of your fans.

358
00:29:09,021 --> 00:29:10,658
I don't know what you
told them on the flight,

359
00:29:10,658 --> 00:29:12,413
but you made quite an impression
a big impression.

360
00:29:12,413 --> 00:29:13,971
Especially on Forestier.

361
00:29:13,971 --> 00:29:15,349
Huge!

362
00:29:15,464 --> 00:29:17,442
Will you see them?

363
00:29:17,442 --> 00:29:20,019
They want me to help them
them back into the company.

364
00:29:20,019 --> 00:29:22,478
If only they'd pour
more water in their wine!

365
00:29:23,362 --> 00:29:25,396
Good night!
- Can I carry your suitcase?

366
00:29:25,396 --> 00:29:27,427
No, monsieur, thank you.
See you tomorrow!

367
00:29:29,859 --> 00:29:31,691
Why are you looking
looking at me like that?

368
00:29:31,691 --> 00:29:35,800
You look unusual.
You seem upset about something.

369
00:29:35,800 --> 00:29:38,185
Only by my fatigue!

370
00:29:39,241 --> 00:29:41,006
Then get a good night's rest!

371
00:29:59,490 --> 00:30:01,120
Hey, time to get up!

372
00:30:03,266 --> 00:30:05,954
So, uh. What's the matter?

373
00:30:05,954 --> 00:30:08,721
Who sleeps till noon
at your age?!

374
00:30:08,721 --> 00:30:12,882
The maid has to clean
the bedrooms! Hey, get up!

375
00:30:13,560 --> 00:30:15,190
Oh, you look great!

376
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,187
No, I mean, what's the big deal
dragging people around.

377
00:30:17,187 --> 00:30:19,173
without warning
from your own bed?!

378
00:30:19,173 --> 00:30:22,352
You're gonna have a heart attack!
